Yeah.

267
00:25:44,928 --> 00:25:47,421
I do. Don't worry, Pun.

268
00:25:49,671 --> 00:25:52,468
Has Nano ever borrowed money from you, Earn?

269
00:25:53,592 --> 00:25:55,899
Yeah, she has.

270
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:57,652
But not that much.

271
00:25:58,733 --> 00:26:00,173
How much is not that much?

272
00:26:00,948 --> 00:26:03,456
About the same as what she borrowed from you.

273
00:26:03,936 --> 00:26:05,498
And has she paid you back yet?

274
00:26:08,535 --> 00:26:11,099
I really want to know what she's doing with the money.

275
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:13,732
It's been a month, man, and she still hasn't paid me back.

276
00:26:13,732 --> 00:26:15,308
Her family seems rich too, right?

277
00:26:17,303 --> 00:26:19,768
I've seen Nano taking care of a lot of stray cats.

278
00:26:19,769 --> 00:26:22,768
She also mentioned that cat food is really expensive.

279
00:26:22,769 --> 00:26:26,455
She feels sorry for them and doesn't want to leave them on the street.

280
00:26:26,973 --> 00:26:29,580
And her family doesn't support her buying cat food.

281
00:26:31,008 --> 00:26:32,995
Is it really just for raising cats?

282
00:26:44,121 --> 00:26:45,990
Guess who?

283
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:49,852
Hey, shouldn't I be the one asking that?

284
00:26:55,603 --> 00:26:57,316
I just said it for you.

285
00:26:57,536 --> 00:26:58,916
So you wouldn't have to tire yourself out.

286
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:03,308
If I didn't want to get tired,

287
00:27:03,574 --> 00:27:05,368
I probably wouldn't have come to see you, right?

288
00:27:16,253 --> 00:27:18,297
I'm really busy today.

289
00:27:18,298 --> 00:27:19,943
I need to hurry up and go.

290
00:27:21,084 --> 00:27:22,731
You're busy every day.

291
00:27:23,124 --> 00:27:24,888
More like you're bored of me.

292
00:27:26,314 --> 00:27:27,700
I'm not bored.

293
00:27:31,353 --> 00:27:32,660
Normally,

294
00:27:33,483 --> 00:27:35,734
I never really think too much about you.

295
00:27:36,657 --> 00:27:41,299
But I don't know why, lately my feelings have been strange.

296
00:27:43,598 --> 00:27:46,073
I mean, we've had this secret thing going on for so long.

297
00:27:47,223 --> 00:27:49,697
And I only do this kind of thing with you.

298
00:27:50,207 --> 00:27:51,587
I think...

299
00:27:53,578 --> 00:27:55,064
I'm catching feelings.

300
00:27:57,764 --> 00:28:00,784
And you probably feel the same way, right?

301
00:28:02,685 --> 00:28:04,545
What you said on that show...

302
00:28:05,620 --> 00:28:07,809
My name is Sasikamol.

303
00:28:08,444 --> 00:28:09,884
It starts with an 'S' too.

304
00:28:11,814 --> 00:28:13,314
Did you mean me?

305
00:28:38,819 --> 00:28:39,919
Earn.

306
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:41,819
Where's Belle?

307
00:28:43,543 --> 00:28:45,745
She probably went to the restroom.

308
00:28:46,085 --> 00:28:48,197
In the restroom for the whole period?

309
00:28:55,957 --> 00:28:58,391
Here, at the end of the period,

310
00:28:58,392 --> 00:29:01,102
please collect everyone's exercises and leave them at the front of the room.

311
00:29:01,102 --> 00:29:02,274
I'll be right back.

312
00:29:02,275 --> 00:29:03,675
And please hand these out too.

313
00:30:02,716 --> 00:30:04,283
Why aren't you in class?

314
00:30:04,284 --> 00:30:05,530
I don't feel like it.

315
00:30:10,236 --> 00:30:11,842
Smoking is not allowed here.

316
00:30:12,857 --> 00:30:14,063
I know.

317
00:30:14,738 --> 00:30:16,413
But I don't care.

318
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:19,173
Rules aren't meant to be followed all the time, right?

319
00:30:19,302 --> 00:30:21,017
Learn to follow your heart sometimes.

320
00:30:21,863 --> 00:30:24,713
Do you know how? If not, I can teach you.

321
00:30:36,437 --> 00:30:38,066
Before you try teaching me...

322
00:30:38,159 --> 00:30:39,639
go back to your class.

323
00:31:20,364 --> 00:31:22,745
[Did you transfer money? 20,000 baht?]

324
00:31:27,344 --> 00:31:29,382
[It's my savings from tutoring.]

325
00:31:29,383 --> 00:31:32,749
[I'll give it to Dad for the car repair first. Don't worry.]

326
00:31:44,486 --> 00:31:45,539
Jane.

327
00:31:45,956 --> 00:31:47,116
Are you here to read?

328
00:31:48,247 --> 00:31:49,487
No.

329
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:52,660
My notebook got torn.

330
00:31:56,176 --> 00:31:59,350
I thought I'd come borrow some tape from the teacher around here to fix it.

331
00:31:59,690 --> 00:32:01,350
I don't know where they are.

332
00:32:05,388 --> 00:32:07,023
Jane, you can tell me anything.

333
00:32:08,258 --> 00:32:10,989
Even though I might not be able to help much,

334
00:32:10,990 --> 00:32:12,595
you can really talk to me.

335
00:32:15,958 --> 00:32:17,438
Thank you, Earn.

336
00:32:19,495 --> 00:32:22,532
I really don't know what I did wrong.

337
00:32:23,032 --> 00:32:26,371
Why do they have to bully me like this?

338
00:32:29,861 --> 00:32:31,021
You're not wrong, Jane.

339
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:32,949
The people bullying you are.

340
00:32:33,844 --> 00:32:34,991
Don't be discouraged.

341
00:32:39,065 --> 00:32:40,605
Let me see.

342
00:32:43,492 --> 00:32:45,652
It's torn up so badly.

343
00:32:45,945 --> 00:32:49,675
I think I'll go find a big book to press it flat.

344
00:32:49,676 --> 00:32:53,043
Hey, it's okay, I'll go look for one myself.

345
00:32:59,658 --> 00:33:02,127
The encyclopedias are over there.

346
00:33:02,867 --> 00:33:04,172
Oh.

347
00:33:04,173 --> 00:33:05,899
Okay, okay, I'll be right back.

348
00:33:21,127 --> 00:33:22,989
Hey, someone's coming.

349
00:33:22,989 --> 00:33:24,076
Run!

350
00:33:27,091 --> 00:33:28,104
What?

351
00:33:28,771 --> 00:33:30,046
What the...?

352
00:33:31,659 --> 00:33:32,953
What are you doing?

353
00:33:33,222 --> 00:33:35,716
Oh, hi.

354
00:33:37,917 --> 00:33:39,404
Amy, right?

355
00:33:41,021 --> 00:33:43,665
Oh, I went to hear you sing the other day.

356
00:33:43,666 --> 00:33:46,244
Wow, you were really awesome.

357
00:33:46,245 --> 00:33:47,590
Thanks.

358
00:33:50,849 --> 00:33:52,382
Oh, this is my friend.

359
00:33:52,908 --> 00:33:55,841
She just went through a breakup, she's crying.

360
00:33:56,209 --> 00:33:57,509
Cry!

361
00:34:02,752 --> 00:34:04,638
She doesn't really want anyone to see her face.

362
00:34:05,498 --> 00:34:07,901
Okay, okay. I won't bother you guys then.

363
00:34:07,902 --> 00:34:09,328
I'll get going now.

364
00:34:11,150 --> 00:34:13,063
Cheer up!

365
00:34:25,276 --> 00:34:27,029
Your hair is a mess.

366
00:34:27,271 --> 00:34:28,745
Did it look natural?

367
00:34:29,078 --> 00:34:30,118
Maybe.

368
00:34:33,383 --> 00:34:36,436
Sorry I'm late. I ran into someone I knew.

369
00:34:37,562 --> 00:34:40,251
Hmm, you have a friend now, Jane?

370
00:34:40,251 --> 00:34:41,730
We just met.

371
00:34:44,986 --> 00:34:46,445
By the way, Earn,

372
00:34:46,446 --> 00:34:50,503
how do the cheer stand and the cheerleaders usually split the budget?

373
00:34:50,816 --> 00:34:53,840
Actually, other color teams usually split it evenly.

374
00:34:53,841 --> 00:34:57,650
But our team usually wins the cheerleader more than the cheer stand.

375
00:34:57,651 --> 00:35:00,344
So we split it 60/40.

376
00:35:00,837 --> 00:35:03,683
But sometimes even 70.

377
00:35:04,289 --> 00:35:05,543
Whoa!

378
00:35:06,049 --> 00:35:08,713
Why do cheerleaders have so many expenses?

379
00:35:08,714 --> 00:35:12,474
I'm not exactly sure, but from what I've seen,

380
00:35:12,475 --> 00:35:18,328
it's mostly for off-campus practice venues, costumes,

381
00:35:18,329 --> 00:35:21,867
or hair and makeup on the sports day, things like that.

382
00:35:21,868 --> 00:35:23,771
But I don't know about the rest.

383
00:35:25,703 --> 00:35:28,169
Then it's okay. I'll go talk to Nano myself.

384
00:35:30,502 --> 00:35:31,874
Need my help?

385
00:35:58,693 --> 00:35:59,766
Hey!

386
00:35:59,767 --> 00:36:00,899
Watch out!

387
00:36:02,106 --> 00:36:03,172
Shit!

388
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:06,356
Hey, I'm so sorry.

389
00:36:07,216 --> 00:36:08,493
Does it hurt a lot?

390
00:36:09,968 --> 00:36:11,995
Hey, go get some ice for a cold compress.

391
00:36:23,274 --> 00:36:24,763
Does it hurt a lot?

392
00:36:25,688 --> 00:36:27,296
It doesn't hurt much now.

393
00:36:30,299 --> 00:36:32,613
And I don't feel anything at all.

394
00:36:35,209 --> 00:36:37,282
Do you want to go to the doctor?

395
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:47,564
Keep the compress on, it won't heal.

396
00:36:59,418 --> 00:37:02,096
Nano, I'd like to split the budget between the cheerleaders and the stand.

397
00:37:02,097 --> 00:37:04,047
Can we do 50/50 like the other teams?

398
00:37:04,048 --> 00:37:05,846
The cheer stand taking 20 is enough.

399
00:37:08,723 --> 00:37:11,034
Our group usually wins the cheerleader trophy all the time.

400
00:37:11,035 --> 00:37:13,660
But the cheer stand is always last, there's no need to invest in it.

401
00:37:14,048 --> 00:37:16,323
20 is barely enough for welfare expenses alone.

402
00:37:19,317 --> 00:37:21,192
There won't be that many people joining the stand anyway.

403
00:37:22,165 --> 00:37:24,041
But then we wouldn't have enough money for cutouts.

404
00:37:24,042 --> 00:37:25,394
Then scale it down.

405
00:37:27,810 --> 00:37:29,335
Then can you give me a breakdown?

406
00:37:29,336 --> 00:37:31,867
What exactly do the cheerleaders need, and how much budget?

407
00:37:33,820 --> 00:37:35,195
Just for the costumes,

408
00:37:35,196 --> 00:37:36,995
we always have to pay out of our own pockets every year.

409
00:37:36,996 --> 00:37:38,696
Not to mention the hair and makeup artists.

410
00:37:39,229 --> 00:37:42,031
All of that already exceeds 70%.

411
00:37:42,684 --> 00:37:44,312
Then you scale it down.

412
00:37:50,540 --> 00:37:51,873
You're determined, aren't you?

413
00:37:52,375 --> 00:37:53,955
The highlight of our school's sports day

414
00:37:54,483 --> 00:37:56,185
is the cheerleaders.

415
00:37:57,408 --> 00:38:00,043
No one wants to scream their lungs out singing cheer songs.

416
00:38:01,010 --> 00:38:03,492
Since you just transferred here, learn to adapt.

417
00:38:05,764 --> 00:38:07,304
Don't be annoying.

418
00:38:13,982 --> 00:38:16,737
Then I'll go ask the juniors who wants to be on the stand.

419
00:38:16,738 --> 00:38:18,763
And I'll calculate the budget based on the actual numbers.

420
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:20,640
Try me.

421
00:38:30,248 --> 00:38:33,102
This will be what our stand looks like this year.

422
00:38:33,102 --> 00:38:35,898
Time Travel... it can go back in time, like

423
00:38:35,899 --> 00:38:38,387
time machines, dinosaurs, or like

424
00:38:38,388 --> 00:38:42,699
you could dress up as any character from the past.

425
00:38:42,700 --> 00:38:45,336
So whoever wants to be on the stand or wants to help make props,

426
00:38:45,337 --> 00:38:46,863
just let me know.

427
00:38:46,864 --> 00:38:48,184
P'Jane.

428
00:38:48,185 --> 00:38:51,258
If our whole class wants to be on the stand, will there be enough seats?

429
00:38:54,068 --> 00:38:55,171
Wow, the whole class?

430
00:38:55,172 --> 00:38:58,808
Yeah, of course there's enough! Definitely enough. Sure!

431
00:39:02,773 --> 00:39:05,004
So many juniors want to be on the stand.

432
00:39:05,005 --> 00:39:08,054
I guess the cheer budget needs to be doubled.

433
00:39:08,934 --> 00:39:11,415
I don't think 50/50 is going to work anymore.

434
00:39:17,094 --> 00:39:18,602
Hey everyone.

435
00:39:18,603 --> 00:39:21,868
Thank you so much for joining the cheer stand this year.

436
00:39:24,404 --> 00:39:28,941
But with this, we probably won't have much budget left to help the cheerleaders.

437
00:39:29,408 --> 00:39:32,867
But I still want to watch P'Nano and the cheerleaders dance beautifully!

438
00:39:32,868 --> 00:39:36,230
Yeah! The cheerleaders are the pride of our group!

439
00:39:41,762 --> 00:39:43,504
We'll try our best.

440
00:39:44,010 --> 00:39:46,661
But it might not be as grand as previous years.

441
00:40:04,794 --> 00:40:06,262
P'Jane.

442
00:40:06,263 --> 00:40:07,556
What is it?

443
00:40:07,943 --> 00:40:11,229
My friends and I are backing out.

444
00:40:11,535 --> 00:40:14,943
I have friends who are cheerleaders, and I want them to be able to do their best.

445
00:40:14,944 --> 00:40:16,998
If we don't join the stand,

446
00:40:16,999 --> 00:40:19,511
the cheerleaders will get their budget back, right?

447
00:40:20,645 --> 00:40:22,932
Um... yeah.

448
00:40:22,933 --> 00:40:24,718
I'm sorry, P'Jane.

449
00:40:49,288 --> 00:40:51,941
Hello, P'Amy.

450
00:41:02,681 --> 00:41:04,947
We're shooting a school promotional video.

451
00:41:04,948 --> 00:41:06,337
Clip it nicely.

452
00:41:27,815 --> 00:41:29,261
Hello, ma'am.

453
00:41:30,621 --> 00:41:32,185
Oh, hello ma'am.

454
00:41:33,580 --> 00:41:36,467
Hello, teacher. Hello, ma'am.

455
00:41:36,467 --> 00:41:37,621
Thank you.

456
00:41:45,032 --> 00:41:46,665
I just dropped by to say hi to Teacher Thip

457
00:41:46,666 --> 00:41:49,096
and brought some snacks for everyone.

458
00:41:49,097 --> 00:41:50,730
Enjoy.

459
00:41:50,731 --> 00:41:52,276
Thank you.

460
00:41:55,497 --> 00:41:57,973
Amy looks very proper today.

461
00:41:58,739 --> 00:42:00,544
Are you here to receive an award too?

462
00:42:02,329 --> 00:42:05,763
Today, the school selected exemplary student representatives, ma'am.

463
00:42:05,764 --> 00:42:08,945
Both from the academic and extracurricular sides

464
00:42:08,946 --> 00:42:11,246
to shoot a promotional VTR.

465
00:42:12,053 --> 00:42:15,450
Watawan here is the representative for outstanding extracurricular activities.

466
00:42:15,896 --> 00:42:19,693
The song she composed herself is actually going viral right now.

467
00:42:22,721 --> 00:42:25,152
Um, ma'am, excuse me.

468
00:42:25,153 --> 00:42:28,534
If you're ready, could I interview you first?

469
00:42:28,534 --> 00:42:29,870
Sure.

470
00:42:29,871 --> 00:42:31,177
This way, please.

471
00:42:31,178 --> 00:42:32,592
Please.

472
00:42:33,967 --> 00:42:35,961
Ma'am, how important do you think the smart library

473
00:42:35,962 --> 00:42:39,624
is to the education of students like us?

474
00:42:39,624 --> 00:42:41,764
I think it's very important.

475
00:42:41,765 --> 00:42:43,208
Because kids these days

476
00:42:43,209 --> 00:42:46,201
can all find information online.

477
00:42:46,201 --> 00:42:49,941
I probably can't compete with the younger generation when it comes to technology.

478
00:42:49,941 --> 00:42:52,683
So, I'd like to make a contribution

479
00:42:52,683 --> 00:42:56,591
towards purchasing and developing educational equipment.

480
00:42:56,591 --> 00:42:59,482
I'll hand it over to the committee and the teachers

481
00:42:59,483 --> 00:43:03,787
to allocate and purchase for the school.

482
00:43:03,788 --> 00:43:06,392
This contribution I'm making

483
00:43:06,393 --> 00:43:08,958
will hopefully help the students

484
00:43:08,959 --> 00:43:11,473
further their education.

485
00:43:11,474 --> 00:43:14,002
Ma'am, do you have a message for students

486
00:43:14,003 --> 00:43:16,456
who are considering enrolling here?

487
00:43:16,457 --> 00:43:20,396
This is a school that teaches students to be well-mannered

488
00:43:20,397 --> 00:43:24,340
and to be proper young ladies, as they should be.

489
00:43:24,341 --> 00:43:29,180
Come join our Anna Patronage Tipwan family.

490
00:43:29,565 --> 00:43:30,824
For P'Sophie,

491
00:43:30,825 --> 00:43:34,623
how should a proper young lady behave nowadays?

492
00:43:35,081 --> 00:43:37,550
The most important thing for every student,

493
00:43:37,551 --> 00:43:39,995
whether now or in the past,

494
00:43:39,996 --> 00:43:42,050
is simply to know your duties

495
00:43:42,051 --> 00:43:44,183
and fulfill them to the best of your ability,

496
00:43:44,184 --> 00:43:46,206
without causing trouble for anyone.

497
00:43:46,460 --> 00:43:49,566
That, to me, is considered being a proper young lady.

498
00:43:49,567 --> 00:43:51,058
And how does this school help

499
00:43:51,059 --> 00:43:54,890
further students' interests outside of academics?

500
00:43:54,891 --> 00:43:58,695
Actually, our school supports extracurricular activities quite a lot.

501
00:43:58,696 --> 00:44:00,475
But beyond that,

502
00:44:00,476 --> 00:44:04,162
we have a parent association that constantly encourages students

503
00:44:04,163 --> 00:44:08,615
and fully supports us with equipment.

504
00:44:08,616 --> 00:44:11,612
Which I think is a really lovely thing.

505
00:44:12,199 --> 00:44:16,078
Um, computers at other schools might be just for doing reports,

506
00:44:16,079 --> 00:44:19,642
but our school's computers also have music production software installed.

507
00:44:19,643 --> 00:44:22,200
So I consider this award I received today

508
00:44:22,201 --> 00:44:25,773
to be mine and everyone's who helped vote for me.

509
00:44:25,774 --> 00:44:29,670
Including you too, ma'am. Thank you.

510
00:44:29,782 --> 00:44:31,562
Thank you.

511
00:44:34,810 --> 00:44:36,450
This friend of yours is quite nice.

512
00:44:37,015 --> 00:44:39,857
I see her coming over every day for you to tutor her.

513
00:44:39,858 --> 00:44:42,151
I thought she'd be a slacker.

514
00:44:43,806 --> 00:44:45,724
Amy is a smart person.

515
00:44:45,725 --> 00:44:49,261
She might fall behind in class sometimes because she does a lot of activities,

516
00:44:49,841 --> 00:44:51,938
but whatever she's interested in,

517
00:44:52,218 --> 00:44:53,968
she excels at it.

518
00:45:05,239 --> 00:45:07,108
How should we edit this?

519
00:45:07,861 --> 00:45:10,726
There's a part where there's a lot of dead air.

520
00:45:10,726 --> 00:45:13,838
Oh, P'Amy. I thought you had already gone home.

521
00:45:13,839 --> 00:45:16,538
Wow, your answers today were so good!

522
00:45:16,539 --> 00:45:18,986
If I were P'Sophie's mom, I'd be so thrilled.

523
00:45:18,987 --> 00:45:20,805
Wow, really?

524
00:45:20,806 --> 00:45:21,929
Yeah!

525
00:45:21,930 --> 00:45:23,397
Hey, Aioon.

526
00:45:23,398 --> 00:45:25,901
Why don't you let P'Amy help check the pacing of the edit?

527
00:45:25,902 --> 00:45:28,745
I'm going to go lock the club room door first, in case I forget.

528
00:45:28,746 --> 00:45:29,573
Okay.

529
00:45:29,575 --> 00:45:30,813
I'll get going now.

530
00:45:35,168 --> 00:45:37,591
Are you fully recovered?

531
00:45:37,592 --> 00:45:39,516
You're even here helping shoot content today.

532
00:45:39,517 --> 00:45:43,612
It still hurts a bit, but it's okay.

533
00:45:43,613 --> 00:45:45,120
You're so hardworking.

534
00:45:45,121 --> 00:45:47,046
Do you want to be the club president like Anna?

535
00:45:48,139 --> 00:45:52,638
I just wanted to try shooting content, so I came to help.

536
00:45:52,639 --> 00:45:55,722
I like filming when you guys are doing activities.

537
00:45:55,723 --> 00:45:57,031
Really?

538
00:45:57,032 --> 00:46:00,513
So among all the things you've filmed, are there any behind-the-scenes of me?

539
00:46:06,452 --> 00:46:07,900
There's a lot.

540
00:46:09,834 --> 00:46:12,157
You do so many activities,

541
00:46:12,158 --> 00:46:14,717
and you're so talented.

542
00:46:18,090 --> 00:46:22,803
Actually, I've had a crush on you too.

543
00:46:22,804 --> 00:46:27,018
At first, I thought it was just like a regular fan admiring you,

544
00:46:27,019 --> 00:46:29,004
like everyone else.

545
00:46:29,512 --> 00:46:30,640
But...

546
00:46:31,367 --> 00:46:35,164
after seeing you do so many things,

547
00:46:35,823 --> 00:46:39,713
I felt like I wanted to get to know you better.

548
00:46:41,489 --> 00:46:46,221
I'm glad you hit me in the face with that basketball that day.

549
00:46:46,222 --> 00:46:48,384
It gave us a chance to talk.

550
00:46:50,045 --> 00:46:53,060
And today you even came to talk to me first.

551
00:46:57,921 --> 00:47:01,415
I just wanted to tell you how I feel.

552
00:47:02,049 --> 00:47:07,507
Even if you already have someone you like, it's okay.

553
00:47:12,220 --> 00:47:13,950
Thank you so much.

554
00:47:14,197 --> 00:47:16,091
You're so cool, Aioon,

555
00:47:16,092 --> 00:47:18,132
for being brave enough to confess to me directly.

556
00:47:18,133 --> 00:47:20,757
I don't even have the courage to tell someone I like them directly like this.

557
00:47:21,787 --> 00:47:24,483
From now on, if you need my help with anything,

558
00:47:24,484 --> 00:47:28,419
or if you want some advice, you can reach out to me anytime, okay?

559
00:47:28,420 --> 00:47:30,271
Don't hesitate at all.

560
00:47:33,826 --> 00:47:36,637
Now, show me the video. I'll help you edit it.

561
00:47:36,638 --> 00:47:37,677
Okay!

562
00:48:02,952 --> 00:48:05,580
[@Nalin A student from Class 11C skipped school this afternoon.]

563
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:08,591
[Teacher Nalin, were you not aware of this?]

564
00:48:14,435 --> 00:48:17,050
[Even though you are a new homeroom teacher,]

565
00:48:17,050 --> 00:48:19,850
[please take good care of your students.]

566
00:48:38,593 --> 00:48:39,737
I have exams coming up.

567
00:48:39,738 --> 00:48:42,979
Do you even study? Please, at least read a little.

568
00:48:44,867 --> 00:48:46,995
By the way, what should we eat?

569
00:48:48,774 --> 00:48:51,803
"Whatever" again? Then you choose.

570
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:55,730
Not this one.

571
00:48:55,999 --> 00:48:57,465
Let's have something Japanese.

572
00:49:04,788 --> 00:49:06,250
Not this one.

573
00:49:07,511 --> 00:49:09,311
May I speak with Belle for a moment?

574
00:49:20,244 --> 00:49:21,798
If you're going to break the rules,

575
00:49:22,538 --> 00:49:24,324
why do it in a way where you get caught?

576
00:49:26,966 --> 00:49:28,894
Just in case you didn't know, teacher...

577
00:49:29,816 --> 00:49:32,311
I'm the Mother Superior's biological niece.

578
00:49:33,828 --> 00:49:35,308
That means...

579
00:49:35,683 --> 00:49:37,601
no matter how badly I behave,

580
00:49:37,602 --> 00:49:40,155
or how much I want to get expelled,

581
00:49:40,628 --> 00:49:42,337
my aunt will never expel me.

582
00:49:43,065 --> 00:49:45,980
So you don't need to care about me.

583
00:49:46,975 --> 00:49:48,835
Just leave it between me and my aunt.

584
00:49:51,757 --> 00:49:55,137
I don't care about your personal life.

585
00:50:01,355 --> 00:50:04,841
But I pity your skills.

586
00:50:04,842 --> 00:50:06,927
If you want the school to stop targeting you,

587
00:50:06,927 --> 00:50:12,724
prove yourself in the right way.

588
00:50:15,403 --> 00:50:18,863
I don't think I have to prove myself,

589
00:50:20,133 --> 00:50:22,888
especially in this stupid school.

590
00:50:23,088 --> 00:50:27,716
Do you really not know what freedom is?

591
00:50:27,717 --> 00:50:30,478
If you really want freedom,

592
00:50:30,479 --> 00:50:34,817
you wouldn't act in a way that makes people constantly try to control you.

593
00:50:35,270 --> 00:50:37,568
The more you act out,

594
00:50:37,569 --> 00:50:40,216
the more you're just demanding attention.

595
00:50:42,853 --> 00:50:45,282
I know that at this school,

596
00:50:45,514 --> 00:50:47,661
there are a lot of things that don't make sense.

597
00:50:47,976 --> 00:50:50,778
It's very different from your old school environment.

598
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:52,860
Stop running away,

599
00:50:53,180 --> 00:50:56,046
and try to actually beat the Mother Superior, how about that?

600
00:50:57,734 --> 00:50:59,223
What do you mean?

601
00:50:59,223 --> 00:51:03,188
If you agree to compete in the French contest and win,

602
00:51:03,188 --> 00:51:05,341
I'll talk to the Mother Superior for you.

603
00:51:05,341 --> 00:51:07,421
I'll suggest she transfer you back to an international school

604
00:51:07,422 --> 00:51:09,372
where my friend teaches.

605
00:51:09,373 --> 00:51:11,698
There's a scholarship to study abroad.

606
00:51:12,166 --> 00:51:14,657
If you really want to escape your aunt,

607
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:16,745
this is a great option.

608
00:51:17,118 --> 00:51:19,105
Or even if you don't want to go,

609
00:51:19,106 --> 00:51:23,122
it's an excuse with enough weight to make the Mother Superior

610
00:51:23,122 --> 00:51:24,789
accept you.

611
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:32,646
And who are you? Why would my aunt listen to you?

612
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:36,062
Before you can make the Mother Superior believe in you,

613
00:51:37,349 --> 00:51:38,789
you have to believe in me first.

614
00:51:54,911 --> 00:51:57,750
Do you have any plans for celebrating this Saturday?

615
00:51:59,507 --> 00:52:00,827
This Saturday?

616
00:52:02,690 --> 00:52:06,676
Don't tell me you studied so hard you forgot your own birthday.

617
00:52:08,090 --> 00:52:09,403
Oh.

618
00:52:09,690 --> 00:52:11,197
You're right.

619
00:52:11,310 --> 00:52:13,588
If you don't know where to go yet,

620
00:52:13,589 --> 00:52:17,497
should we go to my friend's resort? The one we went to last year.

621
00:52:18,421 --> 00:52:20,330
Sure, if you want to go.

622
00:52:20,891 --> 00:52:22,418
Invite Amy along too.

623
00:52:23,093 --> 00:52:27,326
It's your birthday, invite your close friend so you can have fun.

624
00:52:27,327 --> 00:52:29,989
And I can get to know Amy better too.

625
00:52:32,648 --> 00:52:34,075
Okay.

626
00:52:42,654 --> 00:52:44,389
I'm here.

627
00:52:46,766 --> 00:52:49,750
I told the doctor we can start the targeted therapy.

628
00:52:51,285 --> 00:52:53,433
And where did you get the money for that, honey?

629
00:52:55,997 --> 00:52:58,319
I have some savings.

630
00:53:06,300 --> 00:53:10,464
My illness is causing you so much trouble.

631
00:53:13,263 --> 00:53:14,856
Don't say that.

632
00:53:13,323 --> 00:53:18,079
What trouble?

633
00:53:18,079 --> 00:53:21,376
When I was a kid, I was sick all the time.

634
00:53:21,377 --> 00:53:23,420
And you never complained.

635
00:53:23,839 --> 00:53:26,023
But now I'm a grown-up.

636
00:53:26,583 --> 00:53:28,618
Anything I can do for you,

637
00:53:29,593 --> 00:53:31,535
please let me do it for you, Mom.

638
00:53:34,652 --> 00:53:38,815
I'll be getting a bonus from the school next month anyway.

639
00:53:39,724 --> 00:53:41,744
As for your medical bills,

640
00:53:42,419 --> 00:53:43,825
I can pay them no matter how much they are.

641
00:53:44,611 --> 00:53:46,178
Don't worry.

642
00:53:47,762 --> 00:53:49,275
Thank you, honey.

643
00:53:55,672 --> 00:53:56,919
You're such a good girl.

644
00:54:27,547 --> 00:54:28,747
Where's Teacher Nalin?

645
00:54:28,842 --> 00:54:30,715
She's probably not coming today.

646
00:54:30,716 --> 00:54:33,803
She said we'll start practicing when we have all 4 people.

647
00:54:37,560 --> 00:54:40,426
So you're here because...?

648
00:54:41,082 --> 00:54:43,062
Yeah, I entered the competition too.

649
00:54:43,223 --> 00:54:44,623
Whoa!

650
00:54:45,977 --> 00:54:47,490
What are you doing?

651
00:54:48,023 --> 00:54:49,787
Just scrolling through my feed.

652
00:54:55,799 --> 00:54:57,007
Is that Amy?

653
00:54:57,008 --> 00:55:00,120
Yeah, she's singing a Marc-Flute song.

654
00:55:00,724 --> 00:55:02,177
Marc-Flute?

655
00:55:03,285 --> 00:55:07,222
Oh, the ship you like, right?

656
00:55:07,591 --> 00:55:09,157
Yeah.

657
00:55:18,776 --> 00:55:23,979
[Even without seeing your face, I can't take it anymore.]

658
00:55:35,983 --> 00:55:37,583
You saw that, right?

659
00:55:40,016 --> 00:55:41,369
Yeah.

660
00:55:49,742 --> 00:55:52,132
Belle, can you please not tell anyone about this?

661
00:55:53,916 --> 00:55:57,222
Who would I even tell?

662
00:56:00,005 --> 00:56:01,625
I won't tell anyone anyway.

663
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:05,924
But you probably think badly of me now, don't you?

664
00:56:08,723 --> 00:56:11,611
Why do you care how I look at you?

665
00:56:18,096 --> 00:56:20,288
What kind of person you are,

666
00:56:20,289 --> 00:56:22,164
you know yourself best.

667
00:56:22,923 --> 00:56:24,257
Have you heard that?

668
00:56:27,526 --> 00:56:32,416
In the end, whether people find out about this in the future or not,

669
00:56:33,489 --> 00:56:34,657
I think

670
00:56:34,911 --> 00:56:38,286
you know best what kind of person you are.

671
00:56:38,900 --> 00:56:40,613
That's the most important thing.

672
00:56:46,530 --> 00:56:48,009
And also...

673
00:56:49,108 --> 00:56:52,034
I've never seen you as a bad person.

674
00:56:53,567 --> 00:56:58,472
I've never met anyone who studies as hard as you.

675
00:56:58,872 --> 00:57:01,656
In this school, you're probably the most frugal person too.

676
00:57:04,915 --> 00:57:06,719
So I think...

677
00:57:08,111 --> 00:57:10,444
you making sex content,

678
00:57:11,532 --> 00:57:14,079
I think you must have your own reasons.

679
00:57:15,459 --> 00:57:18,432
If in the future someone bullies you saying

680
00:57:18,433 --> 00:57:20,151
you do this because you're hungry for money,

681
00:57:20,637 --> 00:57:21,951
tell me.

682
00:57:22,176 --> 00:57:23,910
I'll punch them in the face for you.

683
00:57:27,421 --> 00:57:28,775
Promise me?

684
00:57:29,237 --> 00:57:30,657
That you won't tell anyone.

685
00:57:33,402 --> 00:57:36,324
On the honor of the Mother Superior.

686
00:58:00,070 --> 00:58:03,540
And I'd be happy to hire you immediately.

687
00:58:06,476 --> 00:58:09,306
If you promise me one thing.

688
00:58:10,848 --> 00:58:12,181
What is it?

689
00:58:16,902 --> 00:58:20,306
I want you to get close to the students.

690
00:58:20,905 --> 00:58:23,233
Learn about their personal lives,

691
00:58:23,234 --> 00:58:26,542
or any bad behaviors they are secretly doing.

692
00:58:26,543 --> 00:58:28,096
And report back to me.

693
00:58:28,743 --> 00:58:33,413
So that we can eliminate the problem early on.

694
00:58:34,237 --> 00:58:36,032
But, Mother Superior,

695
00:58:36,033 --> 00:58:39,113
if we use our position as teachers to approach students

696
00:58:39,114 --> 00:58:40,915
with hidden agendas,

697
00:58:41,475 --> 00:58:44,492
isn't that a violation of the students' privacy?

698
00:58:44,893 --> 00:58:48,960
The parents have entrusted us to fully take care of their children.

699
00:58:49,276 --> 00:58:50,751
Therefore,

700
00:58:50,752 --> 00:58:54,176
if there's anything that could damage our school's reputation,

701
00:58:55,680 --> 00:58:58,403
we won't consider it

702
00:58:58,583 --> 00:59:01,220
a private matter for the students at all.

703
00:59:01,547 --> 00:59:04,115
You don't need to worry about anything.

704
00:59:07,387 --> 00:59:10,203
Will you accept my offer, Teacher Nalin?

705
00:59:18,477 --> 00:59:20,548
Well, Teacher Nalin?

706
00:59:20,549 --> 00:59:25,501
Are there any students at risk of ruining our school's reputation?

